WEBVTT

00:07.733 --> 00:10.551
(humming)

00:11.920 --> 00:13.328
-(whirring)
-(grunting)

00:13.330 --> 00:14.513
-(clangs)
-Ow!

00:14.515 --> 00:16.907
Oh, for the love of
absolutely nothing, Toot.

00:16.909 --> 00:18.091
Keep it down!

00:18.093 --> 00:20.352
You're disturbing my customers!

00:20.354 --> 00:21.745
(snoring)

00:21.747 --> 00:23.338
-(squeaks)
-Start the board meeting
without me.

00:23.340 --> 00:25.190
(snoring)

00:25.192 --> 00:26.525
Oops.

00:26.527 --> 00:30.529
Is my new Kawabashi Leaf Ninja
set in show-off mode?

00:30.531 --> 00:34.015
That's 500 CCs
just champing at the bit.

00:34.017 --> 00:35.776
-(revs blower)
-Ow!

00:35.778 --> 00:38.019
My black-market
cochlear implant!

00:38.021 --> 00:40.355
Now let me blow
something else.

00:40.357 --> 00:41.615
Your mind.

00:41.617 --> 00:44.209
Ow! My black market
LASIK surgery!

00:44.211 --> 00:47.695
The youth hockey team
that I sponsor and coach

00:47.697 --> 00:49.214
won the championship this year.

00:49.216 --> 00:53.610
Trophies are what they give
to winners, when they win.

00:53.612 --> 00:55.962
F. Y. I.

00:55.964 --> 00:58.373
Okay, stuff like this
is why Gayle left you.

00:58.375 --> 01:00.617
No one knows why Gayle left me,

01:00.619 --> 01:03.136
except for Gayle
and my more-handsome brother.

01:03.138 --> 01:05.564
But don't let my success
get to you, Moe.

01:05.566 --> 01:08.734
Remember, just because
something good happens to me,

01:08.736 --> 01:10.718
you're a giant loser.

01:10.720 --> 01:13.906
Anyway, just something
for you to stew on.

01:13.908 --> 01:17.725
Right. Sure I am.
Me, stew. No way.

01:17.727 --> 01:20.304
Not stew, not me.
No stew.

01:20.306 --> 01:21.655
-Hey, Stu.
-(chuckles)

01:21.657 --> 01:22.915
Me, stew?

01:22.917 --> 01:26.901
I ain't spending one second
replaying my failures.

01:26.903 --> 01:28.645
(chuckles)

01:28.647 --> 01:31.148
Like how I don't got no money,
I got no education.

01:31.150 --> 01:33.166
My mattress
is a pallet of flyers

01:33.168 --> 01:34.409
I was supposed to deliver.

01:34.411 --> 01:36.820
How I was invited
to five different dinners

01:36.822 --> 01:38.171
for schmucks in one week.

01:38.173 --> 01:40.081
I only got one lightbulb,

01:40.083 --> 01:42.101
which I got to take
from room to room.

01:42.103 --> 01:46.087
How every sex cult I join
turns into a suicide cult.

01:46.089 --> 01:48.941
I'm a speck.
No, I'm-I'm less than a speck.

01:48.943 --> 01:51.426
I'm nothing but, uh...
I'm a scuzz.

01:51.428 --> 01:52.760
Moe, what gives?

01:52.762 --> 01:55.614
You've been dwelling on your
failures for ten months.

01:55.616 --> 01:57.265
Why didn't you stop me?

01:57.267 --> 01:59.526
'Cause then we'd have
to touch your shoulder.

01:59.528 --> 02:00.661
(all shudder)

02:01.938 --> 02:03.864
Soccer season is over.

02:03.866 --> 02:07.108
The conquering
participant returns.

02:07.110 --> 02:09.353
Congratulations, sweetie.

02:09.355 --> 02:12.205
I know how hard you strived
to participate.

02:12.207 --> 02:15.783
It wasn't easy,
but I did the bare minimum.

02:15.785 --> 02:19.045
Thanks for driving me to games
every Saturday, Dad.

02:19.047 --> 02:21.047
Well, I knew
it wouldn't last forever.

02:21.049 --> 02:23.049
And now,
with soccer season over,

02:23.051 --> 02:25.460
sitting season...

02:25.462 --> 02:27.053
begins.

02:27.055 --> 02:28.388
Homer, get up.

02:28.390 --> 02:31.041
Bart's first
junior hockey game is today.

02:31.043 --> 02:33.727
But-but kids' sports was over!

02:33.729 --> 02:36.563
It's great father-son bonding.

02:36.565 --> 02:39.549
No. It's me driving
while Bart looks at his phone.

02:39.551 --> 02:41.827
Then it's Bart playing
while I look at my phone.

02:41.829 --> 02:44.830
Then me driving home while
we both look at our phones.

02:44.832 --> 02:48.392
That's what kids' sports is.

02:48.394 --> 02:50.727
Can I have some money
to bet on the games?

02:50.729 --> 02:52.913
♪

02:52.915 --> 02:54.173
(indistinct chatter)

02:54.175 --> 02:56.082
-(whistle blows)
-Okay, diapers.

02:56.084 --> 02:57.417
I'm gonna tell you something

02:57.419 --> 03:00.404
no coach ever had the heart
to say to his players.

03:00.406 --> 03:04.099
You are only here
to fix my emotional problems.

03:05.186 --> 03:06.351
Yeah!

03:06.353 --> 03:08.836
We're 20 games away
from me getting a trophy

03:08.838 --> 03:11.765
and six payments away
from me owning this whistle.

03:11.767 --> 03:13.767
Now, you all know the game plan.

03:13.769 --> 03:16.010
We suck except Bart,
so give him the stupid puck

03:16.012 --> 03:18.513
and then shut our stupid mouths,
you stupid pukes.

03:18.515 --> 03:20.941
Yeah, good job, uh,
kid who ain't Bart.

03:20.943 --> 03:23.035
Now let's go watch Bart do this!

03:23.037 --> 03:25.762
(cheering)

03:25.764 --> 03:27.664
♪

03:38.460 --> 03:40.552
(scoreboard buzzes)

03:40.554 --> 03:42.596
(cheering)

03:43.632 --> 03:45.615
Oh, you're so done, Toot.

03:45.617 --> 03:47.451
(whoops)

03:47.453 --> 03:49.970
(laughter)

03:49.972 --> 03:52.456
(indistinct chatter)

03:52.458 --> 03:54.233
(whispering)

03:56.720 --> 03:57.885
(grunts)

03:57.887 --> 04:02.148
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ouch...

04:02.150 --> 04:05.635
Oops. My biggest guy
took out your scorer.

04:05.637 --> 04:09.306
Hey, feel free to retaliate
with your biggest kid.

04:09.308 --> 04:11.324
Hmm.

04:11.326 --> 04:14.736
Put me in, Coach.
I'll rip him limb from limb.

04:14.738 --> 04:17.163
(grunting)

04:17.165 --> 04:19.007
Let me at him. (grunts)

04:21.653 --> 04:23.553
(grunting)

04:26.158 --> 04:28.583
-The net ate my hockey cookie.
-(audience cheering)

04:28.585 --> 04:30.394
(crying)

04:31.497 --> 04:33.830
(buzzes)

04:33.832 --> 04:35.983
(groaning)

04:43.675 --> 04:45.617
Wha...

04:45.619 --> 04:47.035
(gasps)

04:47.863 --> 04:49.288
(grunts)

04:49.290 --> 04:52.440
Oh, thank heavens.
An adult has arrived to help me.

04:52.442 --> 04:54.626
No, no, no.
I'm just here to observe.

04:54.628 --> 04:56.019
(grunts)

04:56.021 --> 04:58.188
Uh, how would you like
to play hockey?

04:58.190 --> 05:00.206
Haw-haw... key?

05:00.208 --> 05:02.116
It's the most messed-up sport
in the world.

05:02.118 --> 05:04.528
It's like a prison riot
but with less rules.

05:04.530 --> 05:07.806
And you, you would play
the best position of all--

05:07.808 --> 05:09.382
the goon.

05:09.384 --> 05:10.792
Goon...

05:10.794 --> 05:11.959
Pretty word.

05:11.961 --> 05:13.553
What it mean?

05:13.555 --> 05:17.632
It's that sweet spot between
a thug and an enforcer.

05:17.634 --> 05:20.485
Anyone who comes near
the best players on the team,

05:20.487 --> 05:22.379
the goon turns their face
into mustard.

05:22.381 --> 05:25.231
(chuckles) You're exactly
what my team needs.

05:25.233 --> 05:27.400
Team? I don't do teams.

05:27.402 --> 05:28.735
Sorry.

05:28.737 --> 05:30.387
Not my pierogies!

05:30.389 --> 05:33.165
My Oma makes them
but once a week.

05:33.167 --> 05:35.892
(groans)
I got to deal with this.

05:35.894 --> 05:37.243
Nah, I get it.

05:37.245 --> 05:39.412
People look at scuzzes like us
like we got the plague.

05:39.414 --> 05:42.657
Which, when I did,
it weren't even bubonic.

05:42.659 --> 05:45.827
Our schedule, in case
you change your mind, there.

05:45.829 --> 05:47.161
Maybe we'll both find out

05:47.163 --> 05:49.089
what it feels
like to be winners.

05:49.091 --> 05:51.016
-(grunting)
-Hmm. Hmm. Hmm. Hmm.

05:55.914 --> 05:57.689
Full steam ahead, lads.

05:57.691 --> 05:59.082
We make for the goal,

05:59.084 --> 06:01.676
and damn their
neutral zone trap.

06:01.678 --> 06:03.195
(laughing)

06:03.197 --> 06:06.198
Oh, another weekend
murdered by kids' sports.

06:06.200 --> 06:08.091
How come this is
the only league in the world

06:08.093 --> 06:09.943
without a labor dispute?

06:09.945 --> 06:11.611
Unionize, cowards!

06:11.613 --> 06:13.263
SEA CAPTAIN: Yarr!

06:13.265 --> 06:16.041
(grunts)
I'm getting killed out there!

06:16.043 --> 06:18.118
So you get a little dinged up.

06:18.120 --> 06:20.604
You ever seen the children's
wing at the hospital?

06:20.606 --> 06:23.106
They got murals on the walls.
You'll love it.

06:23.108 --> 06:26.200
Everywhere you look--
rainbow, rainbow, rainbow.

06:26.202 --> 06:27.961
The whole league
knows all they have to do

06:27.963 --> 06:29.554
is beat me up and they win.

06:29.556 --> 06:31.539
Yeah, you're right,
it's hopeless.

06:31.541 --> 06:34.117
There ain't nobody
who's gonna walk into this rink

06:34.119 --> 06:35.727
and turn me into a winner.

06:35.729 --> 06:37.787
No how, no when.

06:37.789 --> 06:40.732
Did somebody order a psycho?

06:40.734 --> 06:41.883
Oh.

06:41.885 --> 06:43.126
Where do you want me, Crotch?

06:43.128 --> 06:45.295
Uh, it-it's "coach."
But just get out there.

06:45.297 --> 06:47.197
Get out there and do your thing.

06:47.983 --> 06:49.482
(grunts)

06:49.484 --> 06:52.369
♪

06:59.586 --> 07:01.661
(buzzing)

07:01.663 --> 07:02.979
-We won!
-We did it!

07:02.981 --> 07:04.089
-Oh, my gosh!
-(cheering)

07:04.091 --> 07:06.483
-My life has meaning!
-(blowing whistle)

07:06.485 --> 07:08.818
As I've been screaming
for the last 15 minutes,

07:08.820 --> 07:12.155
-all players must be
wearing skates.
-Oh, come on.

07:12.157 --> 07:13.581
There's no way that that...

07:13.583 --> 07:15.100
Oh, there it is.

07:15.102 --> 07:17.102
Rule number one:
"No cafeteria trays."

07:17.104 --> 07:19.512
The Bar Flyers forfeit.
The game is over.

07:19.514 --> 07:21.831
ALL:
Aw!

07:21.833 --> 07:23.166
You said I'd get to win.

07:23.168 --> 07:26.111
All I did was make
everyone else a loser, too.

07:26.113 --> 07:30.173
Loser? No, no,
you-you were amazing out there.

07:30.175 --> 07:33.285
-I was?
-Kid, you are
a natural born goon.

07:33.287 --> 07:36.863
A real diamond in the urinal.
All you need is some training.

07:36.865 --> 07:40.292
And I'm gonna make sure
that you learn from the best.

07:41.628 --> 07:44.129
Welcome to Top Goon.

07:44.131 --> 07:45.446
It's beautiful.

07:45.448 --> 07:48.115
I'm gonna learn so hard, Moe.

07:48.117 --> 07:51.761
-I won't let you down.
-I know you won't, kid.

07:53.456 --> 07:56.141
-What was that?
-Oh, I just tousled your hair.

07:56.143 --> 07:58.702
Ain't nobody
ever done that before?

07:58.704 --> 07:59.886
Uh..

07:59.888 --> 08:01.387
Keep going.

08:01.389 --> 08:04.298
Yeah, my arm's getting
a little tired, here.

08:04.300 --> 08:06.568
-That's your problem.
-(sighing): All right.

08:11.066 --> 08:13.233
Welcome to Top Goon.

08:13.235 --> 08:14.493
I'd like to introduce you
to your faculty,

08:14.495 --> 08:17.070
the most feared men
to ever lace 'em up.

08:17.072 --> 08:18.830
Dave "The Hammer" Schultz.

08:18.832 --> 08:20.165
That's just a nickname.

08:20.167 --> 08:23.243
My given name is
<i> David</i> "The Hammer" Schultz.

08:23.245 --> 08:25.337
Stu "The Grim Reaper" Grimson.

08:25.339 --> 08:27.747
I look sane,
but trust me, I'm not.

08:27.749 --> 08:28.990
You'll see.

08:28.992 --> 08:30.842
(growly):
You'll all see.

08:30.844 --> 08:32.326
And Tiger Williams.

08:32.328 --> 08:34.829
Your instructor
for Basic Pummeling

08:34.831 --> 08:36.014
and, time permitting,

08:36.016 --> 08:38.350
The American Novel:
1930 to the Present.

08:38.352 --> 08:39.576
(growls)

08:39.578 --> 08:42.670
As a goon, you have
one job on the ice:

08:42.672 --> 08:44.898
protect your team's best scorer.

08:44.900 --> 08:47.751
We call that person
your "primary."

08:47.753 --> 08:51.196
This is the most important
person in your life.

08:51.198 --> 08:53.757
Who's the best scorer
on your team, Muntz?

08:53.759 --> 08:56.943
-Bart Simpson.
-Then Bart Simpson
is your primary.

08:56.945 --> 08:58.928
Don't forget it.

08:58.930 --> 09:02.115
-Who do we protect?
-ALL: Our primary.

09:02.117 --> 09:04.191
And what do we do
for our primary?

09:04.193 --> 09:05.769
ALL:
Protect them.

09:05.771 --> 09:07.295
And who do we protect?

09:08.698 --> 09:10.031
Our primary?

09:10.033 --> 09:11.775
This kid's good.

09:11.777 --> 09:14.094
("The Hockey Song" by
Stompin' Tom Connors playing)

09:16.464 --> 09:19.299
♪<i> Hello out there,</i>
<i> we're on the air</i> ♪

09:19.301 --> 09:20.967
♪<i> It's hockey night tonight</i> ♪

09:20.969 --> 09:23.544
♪<i> Tension grows,</i>
<i> the whistle blows</i> ♪

09:23.546 --> 09:25.713
♪<i> And the puck goes</i>
<i> down the ice</i> ♪

09:25.715 --> 09:28.308
♪<i> The goalie jumps</i>
<i> and the players bump</i> ♪

09:28.310 --> 09:30.718
♪<i> And the fans all go insane</i> ♪

09:30.720 --> 09:33.129
♪<i> Someone roars,</i>
<i> "Bobby scores!"</i> ♪

09:33.131 --> 09:35.131
♪<i> At the good ol' hockey game</i> ♪

09:35.133 --> 09:37.300
♪<i> Oh, the good ol' hockey game</i> ♪

09:37.302 --> 09:39.469
♪<i> Is the best game</i>
<i> you can name</i> ♪

09:39.471 --> 09:42.563
♪<i> And the best game</i>
<i> you can name</i> ♪

09:42.565 --> 09:44.065
♪<i> Is the good ol'</i>
<i> hockey game.</i> ♪

09:44.067 --> 09:46.251
(groans)

09:46.253 --> 09:47.252
Mm...

09:48.496 --> 09:50.680
Aw...

09:50.682 --> 09:52.498
Huh?

09:52.500 --> 09:53.833
Hey, sorry I'm late.

09:53.835 --> 09:55.819
I couldn't unlock the Maps app.

09:55.821 --> 09:59.005
(chuckling): My phone don't
recognize my face as a face.

09:59.007 --> 10:01.007
I can't believe you came!

10:01.009 --> 10:03.584
I wouldn't miss this
for my own mother's funeral.

10:03.586 --> 10:05.845
I made that choice
and I'm good with it.

10:05.847 --> 10:07.997
Hey, Moe.
How's it going?

10:07.999 --> 10:09.666
You know these guys?

10:09.668 --> 10:12.426
I used to be the bartender
in the penalty box

10:12.428 --> 10:14.187
at the Philadelphia Spectrum.

10:14.189 --> 10:16.506
(chuckles)
My tip jar was full of teeth.

10:16.508 --> 10:19.676
I got Phil Esposito's
whole mouth somewheres.

10:19.678 --> 10:20.785
♪

10:20.787 --> 10:23.513
Muntz, recite the goon code.

10:23.515 --> 10:25.865
I am a goon.
I protect my primary.

10:25.867 --> 10:28.109
And... that's pretty much it.

10:28.111 --> 10:32.021
Nelson Muntz, you've out-thugged
every gorilla in your class.

10:32.023 --> 10:34.633
You are... Top Goon!

10:34.635 --> 10:36.593
♪

10:39.956 --> 10:42.140
I did... not bad?

10:42.142 --> 10:43.683
Hey, you did more than that.

10:43.685 --> 10:45.143
You did not horrible.

10:45.145 --> 10:48.980
Now come on, I got a graduation
present lined up for youse.

10:50.058 --> 10:52.633
From up here,
the wads look like ants.

10:52.635 --> 10:54.969
Hey, you-you want to drop
pickled eggs on them?

10:54.971 --> 10:56.363
Sure!

10:57.399 --> 10:59.382
Yeah, Duff lets me
use their blimp

10:59.384 --> 11:02.402
'cause I buy up all the beer
that the employees drown in.

11:02.404 --> 11:05.330
Pretty sweet
for a couple of scuzzes.

11:05.332 --> 11:08.149
Yeah, it's a big world
down there, kid.

11:08.151 --> 11:09.575
And when its back is turned,

11:09.577 --> 11:12.595
you can steal
anything you want from it.

11:12.597 --> 11:14.655
Oh, that egg just hit
a cop's horse.

11:14.657 --> 11:16.566
Floor it, Jimmy!
Floor it!

11:16.568 --> 11:18.677
(revving)

11:20.071 --> 11:22.222
(moaning)

11:25.911 --> 11:27.519
Great.
I have to drive 50 miles

11:27.521 --> 11:30.263
to spend my entire weekend
freezing my ass off.

11:30.265 --> 11:33.858
Stone-cold sober,
sitting in seats with no backs,

11:33.860 --> 11:37.603
making awkward conversation
with dads who share way too much

11:37.605 --> 11:39.105
about their marriages...

11:39.107 --> 11:42.091
I told Sarah when we got
married, "I am a foot guy."

11:42.093 --> 11:44.093
Please guess the one part
of the body

11:44.095 --> 11:46.187
she just doesn't moisturize?

11:46.189 --> 11:48.039
Seriously, guess.
Guess!

11:48.041 --> 11:51.126
-Please, just guess.
-Oh...

11:55.531 --> 11:59.366
Nelson, could I interest you
in a little skate?

11:59.368 --> 12:02.429
(groans)
I could stretch my legs.

12:04.725 --> 12:05.965
(thudding)

12:05.967 --> 12:08.560
Bart's my primary.
I protect my primary.

12:08.562 --> 12:12.230
What happened here
is a result of your actions.

12:16.478 --> 12:18.311
(scoreboard buzzes)

12:18.313 --> 12:21.147
Wow. Your kid's got real talent.

12:21.149 --> 12:23.299
No-game recognize game, yo.

12:23.301 --> 12:26.486
Shut up! Shut up, all of you!
Don't you see?

12:26.488 --> 12:28.747
There's nothing worse
than your kid being

12:28.749 --> 12:30.081
so amazing at something

12:30.083 --> 12:33.084
you can't blow it off!

12:33.979 --> 12:36.162
So, what's your old lady's

12:36.164 --> 12:37.997
footwear situation at night?

12:37.999 --> 12:39.999
Uh, socks?

12:40.001 --> 12:41.426
No socks?

12:46.825 --> 12:48.825
All right, all right,
tomorrow is the finals.

12:48.827 --> 12:51.269
(whoops)
Hockey's gonna be over!

12:51.271 --> 12:53.663
-If we win,
it's on to the regionals.
-D'oh!

12:53.665 --> 12:54.998
-Then states.
-D'oh!

12:55.000 --> 12:56.349
-Tri-states.
-D'oh!

12:56.351 --> 12:58.668
Quad-states, nationals,
and then tri-nationals.

12:58.670 --> 13:00.503
(moaning)

13:00.505 --> 13:02.763
But first, we take on
King Toots' team.

13:02.765 --> 13:06.192
The same puck-nuts what
humiliated us the last time.

13:06.194 --> 13:08.027
But I know we're gonna
win this game,

13:08.029 --> 13:11.380
because we got
our little hotshot MVP.

13:11.382 --> 13:14.183
That's right,
our Most Violent Puncher.

13:14.185 --> 13:15.752
-Nelson Muntz.
-(gasps)
-Huh?

13:16.797 --> 13:17.796
(Bart grumbles)

13:17.798 --> 13:20.206
(cheering)

13:20.208 --> 13:22.717
I score every goal
on this team.

13:25.305 --> 13:28.364
-(phone chimes)
-And who the hell is texting me?

13:28.366 --> 13:31.384
"Estee Dionne Malip?"

13:31.386 --> 13:34.053
Uh, does anybody know
what this, uh,

13:34.055 --> 13:36.297
"Estee Dionne Malip" is about?

13:36.299 --> 13:38.891
Hey, I'm dealing with
an Estee Dionne Malip?

13:38.893 --> 13:42.061
Anybody? I don't even know
who the hell I got this from.

13:42.063 --> 13:44.714
(groans) I'm just gonna
send it to my junk.

13:44.716 --> 13:46.491
(laughing)

13:46.493 --> 13:49.052
What? What is-what is funny
about that?

13:49.054 --> 13:51.162
-(laughing)
-(grunts)

13:51.164 --> 13:53.164
Show some respect to Coach.

13:53.166 --> 13:55.725
Why? His car is a converted
washing machine

13:55.727 --> 13:57.377
and his wallet is a rat trap.

13:58.913 --> 14:01.064
-(snaps)
-(groaning) Aah!

14:01.066 --> 14:02.990
(laughing)

14:02.992 --> 14:04.917
Simpson's dead.

14:04.919 --> 14:09.180
<i> Bart Simpson is your primary.</i>
<i> Bart Simpson is your primary.</i>

14:09.182 --> 14:11.832
(chuckling):
Oh, he is such a scuzz.

14:11.834 --> 14:13.351
So am I.

14:13.353 --> 14:16.020
You're not my primary.
He is.

14:16.022 --> 14:18.931
-(grunts)
-Ow!

14:18.933 --> 14:19.932
(gasping)

14:19.934 --> 14:22.527
(panting)

14:22.529 --> 14:24.270
-(groaning)
-Doc, is he gonna be all right?

14:24.272 --> 14:28.992
Yes. But I'm afraid his travel
hockey season is over.

14:32.780 --> 14:34.780
(muffled grunt)

14:34.782 --> 14:36.541
(Homer whoops)

14:37.602 --> 14:38.918
(moaning)

14:40.455 --> 14:43.940
What... what have you done?
Bart was our only chance to win.

14:43.942 --> 14:46.459
You were supposed
to protect your primary!

14:46.461 --> 14:48.219
I... I was.

14:48.221 --> 14:50.555
Like hell you was.
Why'd I ever believe in you?

14:50.557 --> 14:53.057
Y-You're just a fist.
Nothing more.

14:53.059 --> 14:54.634
Get off of my team!

14:54.636 --> 14:55.894
(gulps)

14:55.896 --> 14:58.479
Don't look at me.
I'm not crying!

14:59.548 --> 15:01.316
(sobbing)

15:02.477 --> 15:03.735
(grunts)

15:08.149 --> 15:12.226
I just feel like "hockey team"
is still a smidge too big.

15:12.228 --> 15:14.412
Do you have any smaller letters?

15:15.323 --> 15:18.541
I'm no goon.
I'm just a fist.

15:20.828 --> 15:23.496
And this last stop in hell

15:23.498 --> 15:25.214
is where I belong.

15:26.075 --> 15:27.592
(inhales, exhales)

15:30.338 --> 15:32.597
♪

15:33.934 --> 15:35.433
Afternoon there, ma'am.

15:35.435 --> 15:36.993
Uh, I'm Moe Szysl...

15:36.995 --> 15:38.453
Yeah, can you hurry it up?

15:38.455 --> 15:41.439
I got to eat this when
it's fresh off the zapper.

15:41.441 --> 15:42.832
It's about your kid.

15:42.834 --> 15:45.001
I was his hockey coach
and I yelled some stuff

15:45.003 --> 15:47.094
that might have kicked
his heart in the plums.

15:47.096 --> 15:49.113
Oh, so you're
Coach Sizzle-slacks,

15:49.115 --> 15:51.507
the guy he calls his primary.

15:51.509 --> 15:54.193
What? Nelson thinks
I'm his primary?

15:54.195 --> 15:56.512
-You sure about this?
-Yup.

15:56.514 --> 15:59.849
He yelled the whole story
at the window dog.

15:59.851 --> 16:01.517
(growling)

16:01.519 --> 16:03.869
Nelson wasn't being a psycho
towards Bart.

16:03.871 --> 16:06.205
He was being a goon for me.

16:06.207 --> 16:07.614
Do you know where he went?

16:07.616 --> 16:10.042
He said something about
walking the streets.

16:10.044 --> 16:12.695
Coming to a fateful decision
or whatnot.

16:12.697 --> 16:14.138
Eh. Kid stuff.

16:14.140 --> 16:16.516
I got to find him
before he does something crazy.

16:18.720 --> 16:19.978
Nelson Muntz.

16:19.980 --> 16:22.463
Your reputation precedes you.

16:22.465 --> 16:25.132
I hear you're a dingus
to be respected.

16:25.134 --> 16:27.151
I'm just a fist with no code.

16:27.153 --> 16:29.895
Figure I'll be working
for you sooner or later,

16:29.897 --> 16:32.448
so why not get it over with?

16:35.386 --> 16:38.479
I have a gift for smelling out
good henchmen.

16:38.481 --> 16:39.722
(sniffing)

16:39.724 --> 16:42.391
I'm getting hints
of barely-suppressed rage

16:42.393 --> 16:44.410
with top notes
of "nothing matters" and...

16:44.412 --> 16:45.819
(sniffing)

16:45.821 --> 16:49.398
...a deep finish of abandonment
by a male role model.

16:49.400 --> 16:52.235
Smell all you want.
It won't fix anything.

16:52.237 --> 16:53.252
Just tell me who to hurt.

16:53.254 --> 16:55.404
Want me to get him a lead pipe?

16:55.406 --> 16:59.517
Let's start him out easy.
PVC.

17:05.099 --> 17:07.525
How you doing, son?
Can you move?

17:07.527 --> 17:09.435
A little, but it hurts.

17:09.437 --> 17:10.936
I meant can you
move off the couch.

17:10.938 --> 17:14.532
I'm about to enjoy my first
hockey-free weekend in months.

17:14.534 --> 17:16.683
Ooh, hockey!

17:16.685 --> 17:18.494
(grunting)

17:19.764 --> 17:22.932
Homer, get up.
You and Bart are gonna be late.

17:22.934 --> 17:25.376
What? He's useless.
Doc said so.

17:25.378 --> 17:28.028
He can't play any sport
that I have to drive him to.

17:28.030 --> 17:30.882
He has physical therapy,
and the only place

17:30.884 --> 17:34.293
that takes our insurance
is three hours away.

17:34.295 --> 17:37.221
If they ask, Bart is a veteran.

17:37.223 --> 17:38.598
Oh...

17:41.619 --> 17:43.710
Mr. Mayor, I believe
you know the founder

17:43.712 --> 17:47.732
of this vaguely-purposed
yet tax-exempt charity,

17:47.734 --> 17:49.883
my<i> goomar.</i>

17:49.885 --> 17:53.029
Mistresses are the lifeblood
of our community.

17:57.335 --> 17:59.535
Private event.
No pictures.

18:00.396 --> 18:03.247
Well done, Nelly No-Sleeves.

18:04.900 --> 18:06.567
If you'll excuse me,

18:06.569 --> 18:09.812
my men and I have some
perfectly innocent business

18:09.814 --> 18:12.998
to attend to in the back room.

18:13.000 --> 18:15.301
God bless back rooms.

18:16.579 --> 18:17.762
You know why you're here.

18:17.764 --> 18:21.674
You borrow money from me,
I expect to be repaid.

18:21.676 --> 18:24.660
Time to make your bones.

18:24.662 --> 18:26.437
NELSON:
Lead.

18:27.832 --> 18:30.015
This is all I am.

18:30.017 --> 18:31.317
MOE:
Stop!

18:32.687 --> 18:35.504
Nelson, listen to me
before you done did something

18:35.506 --> 18:36.689
you can't done undid.

18:36.691 --> 18:39.024
Whoever's under that hood
don't deserve this.

18:39.026 --> 18:41.602
-They're a human being.
-Moe!

18:41.604 --> 18:44.622
Aw, thank you, old buddy.
(weak chuckle)

18:44.624 --> 18:46.699
Oh, not youse!

18:46.701 --> 18:47.959
You got to help me out.

18:47.961 --> 18:50.035
I only borrowed money
from the mafia

18:50.037 --> 18:52.296
to buy fake birth certificates
for teenagers

18:52.298 --> 18:54.540
so they could play
ten-and-under hockey.

18:54.542 --> 18:57.860
No one deserves a Kansas City
knee job more than this guy,

18:57.862 --> 18:59.378
but that don't matter none.

18:59.380 --> 19:02.365
You swing that pipe,
that's your soul on the line.

19:02.367 --> 19:04.325
You're wasting your time,
"Coach."

19:04.327 --> 19:07.203
You said it yourself:
I'm just a fist.

19:07.205 --> 19:09.054
I know, and that's how
I saw youse at first.

19:09.056 --> 19:10.464
As a weapon.

19:10.466 --> 19:11.798
I was using you,

19:11.800 --> 19:14.393
because I was obsessed
with beating King Toot here.

19:14.395 --> 19:17.229
I knew it.
I'm in your head, bro.

19:17.231 --> 19:20.549
Feed him his own mustache!
No, wait. Don't, don't.

19:20.551 --> 19:22.326
Listen to me.
You're a great kid.

19:22.328 --> 19:25.997
You're determined, selfless,
a real teammate...

19:25.999 --> 19:29.000
And you did for me
what I failed to do for you.

19:29.002 --> 19:31.752
You had my back, scuzz to scuzz.

19:34.565 --> 19:35.822
Aw. (chuckles)

19:35.824 --> 19:37.233
I don't know.

19:37.235 --> 19:40.236
Sometimes, boss, I think
you only see me as a knife.

19:40.238 --> 19:41.420
Did you know I got dreams?

19:41.422 --> 19:43.906
I want to open a gourmet
mac and cheese place

19:43.908 --> 19:45.332
called Louie's Gooey.

19:45.334 --> 19:47.593
And I'm learning Swedish
on a phone app.

19:47.595 --> 19:49.595
But I'm just a gun to you.

19:49.597 --> 19:52.732
Gentlemen, I don't
see you as weapons.

19:54.752 --> 19:56.527
(crying)

19:57.772 --> 20:00.514
Freaking millennials.

20:00.516 --> 20:04.017
Hockey's over, but maybe
we could still do stuff.

20:04.019 --> 20:06.946
You know, like
throw turtles at birds?

20:06.948 --> 20:08.781
Any time you want, kid.

20:08.783 --> 20:10.599
But whatever we do, from now on,

20:10.601 --> 20:13.527
let's leave
the violence behind, uh?

20:13.529 --> 20:15.862
(grunts)
Aah!

20:16.290 --> 20:18.457
Ah.
There you go, kid.

20:18.459 --> 20:20.960
-You earned that.
-No, I haven't.

20:20.962 --> 20:23.462
